nschaften. Ein eigenes Kapitel ist der zweisprachigen Lexikographie Französisch und Deutsch gewidmet.  aThis book provides an in-depth introduction to the theory and practice of French lexicography. The main chapters are devoted to lexicology, lexicography, structures of lexicographic works, the information content of monolingual dictionaries, and French-language dictionaries. The volume serves as a guide for introductory courses on French linguistics and lexicography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aFrench languagexLexicography. 4aFrankophonie. 4aFranzösisch. 4aLexikographie. 4aLexikologie. 4aWörterbücher. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / French.2bisacsh  aDictionaries.  aFrancophonia.  aFrench.  aLexicography.  aLexicology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2014z9783110370270oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831103724100 cprintz978311027258140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028133040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110281330423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110281330/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2014